This article is a transcript of remarks given by President Trump and Secretary of State Mike Pompeo during Pompeo's swearing-in ceremony. President Trump praised Pompeo's qualifications and highlighted his previous service as Director of the Central Intelligence Agency. Pompeo expressed gratitude for the opportunity and outlined his commitment to protecting American security and advancing American interests. He also emphasized the importance of the State Department and expressed his desire to restore its "swagger." Pompeo discussed various foreign policy issues, including the fight against ISIS, relations with Iran and Russia, economic relations with China, and the ongoing negotiations with North Korea. He concluded by expressing his confidence in his team and his eagerness to work with them to accomplish their mission.